{"word":"μηρός","slug":"μηρός","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>μηρός</b></el> <el>(μηρός, οῦ, ὁ,) </el><p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>the thigh</i>, <a href='S:Latin'>Lat.</a> <el>femur</el>, in <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b>in <a href='S:plural'>pl.</a> = <a href='S:μηρία'><el>μηρία</el></a>, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>3. </b>in <a href='S:plural'>pl.</a> also, generally, <i>the leg-bones</i>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}